main event: On June 6, 1959, a civilian in Oakhurst, N.J. reported seeing 11 round, white objects, each about the size of a baseball, traveling in a single file formation with approximately seven minutes of separation. A shadowy object was observed in the vicinity of the first light, described as looking like a plane without wings. The objects appeared from low on the horizon in the southwest, climbed very high, descended to the far horizon in the northeast, hovered over the water, assumed various formations, and then faded out in the northeastern direction.
interesting points: The objects were described as round, white, and the size of a baseball, moving in a single file formation with approximately seven minutes of separation.
A shadowy object was observed in the vicinity of the first light, resembling a plane without wings.

The objects climbed very high, descended to the far horizon, hovered over the water, and assumed various formations, such as a set of dice and a crescent shape, at high altitude and very fast speed before fading out.
The observation lasted for approximately one hour and fifteen minutes.
A preliminary analysis indicated a possibility that a flight of five B-47 aircraft passing through the sighting area could have been the objects sighted.
sighted object: 11 round, white objects, each the size of a baseball
